1
00:00:04,603 --> 00:00:06,614
When we were just in India,

2
00:00:06,614 --> 00:00:09,046
at the new Kolkata airport,

3
00:00:09,046 --> 00:00:12,055
Netaji Subhash
Chandra Bose International …

4
00:00:12,363 --> 00:00:15,222
[Give Me Your Blood!]

5
00:00:15,269 --> 00:00:19,770
and I don’t know where
the Netaji statue is right now,

6
00:00:19,770 --> 00:00:22,308
but it used to be that
when you cleared customs,

7
00:00:22,308 --> 00:00:24,061
there was a statue of Netaji.

8
00:00:24,061 --> 00:00:26,729
They just moved it
to another place probably.

9
00:00:26,729 --> 00:00:33,238
But, he’s this famous freedom fighter,
Bengali freedom fighter,

10
00:00:33,238 --> 00:00:36,270
and there’s a plaque 
underneath him

11
00:00:36,270 --> 00:00:39,056
that Gurudev said Guru Mahārāj
would quote sometimes, and it says,

12
00:00:39,056 --> 00:00:40,672
“Give me your blood

13
00:00:40,672 --> 00:00:43,415
and I’ll give you freedom!”

14
00:00:44,523 --> 00:00:45,852
That was his slogan,

15
00:00:45,852 --> 00:00:49,270
“Give me your blood
and I’ll give you freedom!”

16
00:00:49,270 --> 00:00:51,464
So Guru Mahārāj will say,

17
00:00:51,464 --> 00:00:58,805
“These are the requirements
for things within this world,

18
00:00:58,805 --> 00:01:00,519
so for the ultimate thing,

19
00:01:00,519 --> 00:01:04,936
a position in the ultimate reality,
in Kṛṣṇa consciousness,

20
00:01:04,936 --> 00:01:11,604
will less be required?
Or more?”

21
00:01:11,604 --> 00:01:14,822
So he introduced the concept
of self-dissipation,

22
00:01:14,822 --> 00:01:17,462
as when you make
sandalwood pulp,

23
00:01:17,462 --> 00:01:20,685
you have a grinding stone,
a sandalwood stick,

24
00:01:20,685 --> 00:01:23,020
you pour rosewater 
on the stone,

25
00:01:23,020 --> 00:01:24,771
take the sandalwood stick

26
00:01:24,771 --> 00:01:28,353
and start rubbing it 
into the stone,

27
00:01:28,353 --> 00:01:29,686
and what happens?

28
00:01:29,686 --> 00:01:34,091
Gradually, the sandalwood stick
is dissipating.

29
00:01:34,091 --> 00:01:38,344
That position is finished,
but what’s happening is, this pulp,

30
00:01:38,344 --> 00:01:42,637
this divinely fragrant substance
is being generated

31
00:01:42,637 --> 00:01:46,352
as a consequence of
the self-dissipation.

32
00:01:46,352 --> 00:01:49,507
That’s what Kṛṣṇa consciousness
is meant to be,

33
00:01:49,507 --> 00:01:56,769
that we engage ourselves,
all of our energy and serving capacity,

34
00:01:56,769 --> 00:02:02,021
going against the current
of exploitation,

35
00:02:02,021 --> 00:02:04,603
in a dedicating current,

36
00:02:04,603 --> 00:02:10,077
and through self-dissipation
we’re gradually converted

37
00:02:10,077 --> 00:02:14,816
into a divine position.

38
00:02:14,817 --> 00:02:21,469
So the karmic generating form vanishes,

39
00:02:21,469 --> 00:02:24,819
muktir hitvānyathā rūpaṁ
sva-rūpeṇa vyavasthitiḥ (SB: 2.10.6),

40
00:02:24,819 --> 00:02:32,635
and the golden serving self
begins to express and manifest itself.

41
00:02:32,635 --> 00:02:34,353
Hare Kṛṣṇa.

